com.conceptwave.scripting
Class CatalogQueryResult

com.conceptwave.scripting.Object
  com.conceptwave.scripting.CWScriptable
      com.conceptwave.scripting.CatalogQueryResult

public class CatalogQueryResult
extends CWScriptable

Contains the item codes that match a given search criteria. The search criteria is a CSV string described below. The query results have versions but they are calculated from the beginning of the current day on. The query result is user independent - it is calculated only based on unconditional associations - item-attribute and item-item NOTE: WE DON'T NEED TO RUN QUERY WITH OLDER DATE AS THE HIERARCHY TREE DOES NOT HAVE VERSIONS

Field Detail

errorCount

public com.conceptwave.scripting.Integer errorCount
READONLY: Returns the number of compilation errors for the current query. If there are errors the result length is zero. The errors can be obtained by using the API getErrorCode() and getErrorMessage()

hasPartialResults

public com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean hasPartialResults
READONLY: Returns true if the query result does not contain all items that match the search criteria. The items that are dropped in random even if an order clause is specified. The internal implementation of the query mechanism has limitation which don't allow to process more than 5,000 items in the generic query - the query that has not applied the user specific rules. From business viewpoint however the usable queries should return less than hundred items. The user must specify enough search criteria to narrow the search.

length

public com.conceptwave.scripting.Integer length
READONLY: Returns the number of items in the query result
